        <div class="design-notes">
          <h4>Design Decisions:</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Dark mode:</strong> Reduces eye strain during long monitoring sessions. Violation cards pulse red for instant attention.</li>
            <li><strong>Live feeds:</strong> WebRTC video from each student's desktop app. 320x200px minimum per card (scales to grid).</li>
            <li><strong>Audio indicators:</strong> Animated bars when speaking, muted icon when silent. Teacher can click to unmute/listen.</li>
            <li><strong>One room at a time:</strong> Teacher focuses on single exam. "Switch Room" button opens room selector modal.</li>
            <li><strong>Alerts panel:</strong> Right side, scrollable. Click alert → highlights corresponding video card. Click card → view full details.</li>
            <li><strong>Real-time:</strong> SSE pushes updates. No polling needed. New alerts slide in from right.</li>
            <li><strong>Scalability:</strong> Grid shows 15 students max (3 rows × 5 cols on 1080p). Pagination or room split for larger classes.</li>
          <li><strong>Quick actions:</strong> Each card has Warn/Screenshot/Kick buttons. Actions send signals to student's desktop app instantly via WebSocket.</li>
          <li><strong>Warning flow:</strong> "Warn" sends notification to student's app with violation details. Auto-logs to backend.</li>
          <li><strong>Kick flow:</strong> "Kick" terminates student's exam attempt, forces logout, prevents rejoin. Requires confirmation dialog.</li>
          <li><strong>Screenshot:</strong> Captures current frame from student's feed, stores timestamped image, links to violation record.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
